# Compiler-facing language reference

`docs/language-overview.md` remains the complete compiler-facing language
authority while the public language documentation is split into focused
Beandown references.

## Consolidated authority

Read `docs/language-overview.md` for syntax, semantic invariants, edge cases,
deferred behaviour and the exact outside-scope language surface.

The file remains untouched throughout the migration so every focused
replacement can be checked against one stable baseline.

## Focused references under review

### Loops

Detailed replacements:

- `docs/src/docs/loops/conditional-loops.bd`
- `docs/src/docs/loops/collection-loops.bd`
- `docs/src/docs/loops/range-loops.bd`
- `docs/src/docs/loops/loop-control.bd`

Their paired `-basic.bd` files provide simplified teaching versions.

The public route combines both levels:

`docs/src/docs/loops/#page.bst`

These files are written in the intended final shape. They do not supersede
`docs/language-overview.md` until the complete language migration and parity
review have been approved.

## Public documentation

`docs/src/docs/**` contains website pages, teaching references, examples and
topic navigation.

## Design boundaries

`docs/src/docs/codebase/design-scope/overview.bd` summarises accepted
mechanisms, constraints and intentionally excluded complexity.

## Memory access

`docs/src/docs/codebase/memory-management/access-and-aliasing/overview.bd`
covers shared reads, explicit copies and `~` access.

## Compiler ownership

`docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/overview.bd` routes language features
to the compiler stages and subsystems that implement them.
